00:00:29.673 --> 00:00:32.500
Semia Dahi Vada

00:00:36.215 --> 00:00:38.115
Ingredients required to make Semia Dahi Vada

00:00:38.571 --> 00:00:51.923
Vermicelli, Curd, Maida Flour, Corn Flour, Rice Flour, Curry Leaves, Coriander,
 Green Chillies, Ginger Garlic Paste, Salt, Chilli Powder, Seasoning Seeds, Oil

00:01:03.058 --> 00:01:10.579
Take a pot and heat some water

00:01:13.483 --> 00:01:18.202
Add a cup of vermicelli into the hot water

00:01:37.551 --> 00:01:44.797
Use just enough water to boil the vermicelli

00:01:48.567 --> 00:01:58.611
Add 5 tbsp of rice flour, 1 1/2 tbsp of maida flour

00:02:01.219 --> 00:02:05.703
Add 1 tbsp of corn flour

00:02:15.963 --> 00:02:21.363
Add salt for taste and some curry leaves

00:02:22.841 --> 00:02:31.360
Add some coriander, some ground ginger &amp; green chilli paste

00:02:33.549 --> 00:02:38.685
Mix thoroughly

00:02:45.512 --> 00:02:49.741
If necessary, add more water

00:02:54.204 --> 00:03:01.880
Take a pan and heat some oil for deep frying.
Make small patties with the dough and deep fry them

00:03:18.480 --> 00:03:21.678
Take another pan and heat some oil

00:03:23.345 --> 00:03:30.199
Add some bengal gram, some dry red chilli

00:03:32.677 --> 00:03:35.209
Add some curry leaves.
Switch off the stove

00:03:47.406 --> 00:03:55.084
Take a bowl of curd and add some salt, red chilli powder
and some ginger &amp; green chilli paste

00:04:05.060 --> 00:04:10.953
Add the fried bengal gram and leaves to the curd and mix well

00:04:18.691 --> 00:04:26.329
Add the fried vadas into the curd and let it stand for 5 - 10 mins

00:04:38.693 --> 00:04:44.826
Take the Dahi Vadas into a serving bowl

00:04:55.863 --> 00:05:01.237
Garnish with some coriander

